parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ACD pump can cause the all-wheel drive system to malfunction, leading to loss of traction, reduced handling, and increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud whining noise from the transfer case
and potential failure of the transfer case.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission overheating and power loss can cause the vehicle to lose power, decelerate, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Too Hot Slow Down" warning message appears on the dashboard
the transmission begins to lose power
the transmission runs on high RPM above 3000
and the warning message does not clear even after the vehicle is turned off.
